Y 2025) | 4.4 million (FY 2024) | 2.3 million (FY 2023)\n*   **Starlink ARPU (Average Revenue Per User, dollars per month):**\n    *   $66 (Q1 2026) | $86 (Q1 2025)\n    *   $81 (FY 2025) | $91 (FY 2024) | $99 (FY 2023)\n*   **Satellite Counts & Fleet Size:**\n    *   Approximately 9,600 Starlink broadband and mobile satellites in Low-Earth Orbit (LEO) as of March 31, 2026 (approx. 9,000 broadband satellites).\n    *   Launched approximately 3,100 Starlink broadband and mobile satellites in 2025.\n    *   Accounts for approximately 75% of all active maneuverable satellites in orbit (out of ~12,700 globally).\n    *   Estimated useful life of satellites is three to five years.\n*   **Satellite-to-Mobile Users:** Providing texting and over-the-top voice services to approximately 7.4 million monthly unique devices across approximately 30 countries.\n*   **Network Performance Metrics:**\n    *   Median latency: Approximately 25 milliseconds (as of March 31, 2026).\n    *   Download speeds: Median of 225 Mbps during peak hours for residential users; speeds exceeding 400 Mbps with round-trip latencies as low as 21 milliseconds.\n*   **Next-Gen Capacity:** V3 satellites designed to offer 1 Tbps of downlink capacity per satellite. A single Starship launch will deploy up to 60 V3 satellites (a twenty-fold increase in downlink capacity vs. a Falcon 9 launch).\n*   **Geographic Reach:** 164 countries, territories, and other markets (home to >3.3 billion people).\n*   **MNO Partnerships:** Approximately 30 mobile network operators across six continents.\n\n### **AI Segment (xAI) Metrics**\n*   **Nameplate Compute Draw (in gigawatts):**\n    *   1 GW (Q1 2026) | 0.3 GW (Q1 2025)\n    *   0.8 GW (FY 2025) | 0.3 GW (FY 2024) | 0 GW (FY 2023)\n*   **Monthly Active Users (MAU):** Defined as the total number of users who have interacted with Grok or X at least once in a 30-day period. Methodologies are used to deduplicate users across both platforms so they are not double-counted. (S