        output='Based on the provided financial statement notes and prospectus excerpts, here is the information disclosed regarding the xAI and X mergers, their accounting treatment, and the combined platform strategy:\n\n### 1. Merger Timeline and Structure\n*   **X Merger:** On March 28, 2025, xAI completed its acquisition of X Holdings Corp. (“X”) and X.AI Corp. through a share exchange, making them wholly-owned subsidiaries of xAI. (Twitter, Inc. was previously acquired by Elon Musk in October 2022, and X.AI Corp began operations in March 2023).\n*   **xAI Merger:** On February 2, 2026 (the “xAI Merger Date”), SpaceX completed its acquisition of X.AI Holdings Corp. (“xAI”), making xAI a wholly-owned subsidiary of SpaceX. This was also effected through a share exchange.\n*   **Stock Split:** On May 4, 2026, SpaceX effected a five-for-one forward stock split of its Class A, Class B, and Class C Common Stock. All share and per share information has been retroactively adjusted.\n\n### 2. Common-Control Accounting & Financial Treatment\nBecause Elon Musk had a controlling financial interest and majority voting interest in SpaceX, xAI, and X during the periods presented, the Mergers were accounted for as **reorganizations of entities under common control**. Key accounting impacts include:\n*   **Retrospective Combination:** The consolidated financial statements reflect the retrospective combination of the net assets of the entities at their historical carrying amounts for all periods presented.\n*   **Goodwill and Intangibles:** **No new goodwill or other intangible assets have been recorded** as a result of the mergers.\n*   **Elimination of Intercompany Transactions:** All historical related-party transactions between the entities have been eliminated in consolidation.\n*   **Change in Reporting Entity:** This retrospective presentation constitutes a change in reporting entity. Consequently, separate financial statements of xAI and X are not provided.\n*   **Equity Adjustments:** Capital stock and shareholders\' equity reflect a continuation of historical SpaceX equity combined with X and xAI equity, adjusted by the respective exchange ratios used to effect the mergers.\n*   **Preferred Stock Treatment:** xAI’s historical redeemable convertible preferred stock is presented as such (not recast on an as-converted basis) for all historical periods prior to the xAI Merger. The conversion into SpaceX common stock is recognized prospectively only in Q1 2026 (the period the exchange actually occurred). \n\n### 3. Exchange Ratios\n*   **X Merger:** Each class of X Holdings Corp. common stock was converted to 2.776 shares of xAI common stock. Each class of X.AI Corp. common stock converted to 1.000 share of xAI common stock. X.AI Corp. preferred stock converted to 1.000 share of xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock.\n*   **Presentation:** All historical X, X.AI Corp., and xAI common stock are presented in the financial statements as if converted into SpaceX Common Stock at the applicable exchange rates for all periods presented.\n\n### 4. Qualitative Discussion of Combined Platform Strategy\nSpaceX describes itself as the only company building integrated hardware and software infrastructure across space, connectivity, and AI. The integration of xAI and X is a key pillar of this strategy:\n*   **Vertically Integrated AI:** xAI operates a vertically integrated AI platform spanning the frontier LLM Grok, AI solutions for consumer/enterprise customers, and AI computational infrastructure. SpaceX is rapidly constructing this compute infrastructure—starting on Earth with the goal of extending it to space—at industry-leading pace and cost efficiency.\n*   **Truth-Seeking AI:** Grok is designed as a "truth-seeking" AI model, built on Musk’s mission to enable humanity to understand the universe. Within two years of its initial release, Grok achieved frontier-level performance in scientific reasoning (measured by GPQA Diamond scores).\n*   **Synergy with X:** Grok benefits directly from integration with X (formerly Twitter). X serves as a real-time information, entertainment, and free speech platform that acts as a "foundational distribution and data engine" for SpaceX\'s AI ecosystem, further enhancing Grok’s truth-seeking objectives.\n*   **Overall Mission:** The combined entity aims to make life multiplanetary, understand the true nature of the universe, and extend the light of consciousness to the stars by harnessing the Sun to power a truth-seeking AI. \n\n### 5. Related Party Transactions Incorporated\nFollowing the xAI Merger, ongoing agreements originally entered into by xAI or X Holdings prior to the merger were incorporated into SpaceX\'s related party disclosures. This includes:\n*   **Tesla Agreements:** xAI has commercial, licensing, and support agreements with Tesla (obtaining $506 million in goods/services in 2025). X Holdings has advertising agreements with Tesla. SpaceX also invoices Tesla for aircraft usage.\n*   **The Boring Company:** In 2024, X entered into an office space lease with a subsidiary of The Boring Company.',
