 Subject to customary representations, warranties, covenants, and events of default. Includes a maximum financial covenant requiring a Consolidated Leverage Ratio of no greater than 3.75 to 1.0 at the end of each fiscal quarter (with a temporary step-up to 4.25 to 1.0 for four quarters following a qualifying acquisition of at least $1.0 billion). The company was in compliance as of March 31, 2026.\n    *   **Sublimits:** Up to $150 million for financial letters of credit and up to $1,000 million for performance letters of credit.\n    *   **Status:** No amounts were outstanding as of March 31, 2026, December 31, 2025, or April 30, 2026.\n    *   **Amendments:** In March 2026, the company entered into a First Amendment to Credit Agreement and Waiver in connection with the SpaceX Bridge Loan, which waived certain specified defaults and amended definitions/covenants to conform to the Bridge Loan terms.\n*   **SpaceX ABL Credit Agreement:**\n    *   **Terms:** Entered in 2018 and amended through 2023, it is a senior secured asset-based revolving credit agreement.\n    *   **Capacity:** Up to $1,500 million.\n    *   **Collateral:** Collateralized primarily by a pledge of certain SpaceX inventory and equipment, with availability based on the estimated fair value of such assets less reserves.\n*   **SpaceX Bridge Loan:**\n    *   **Status & Maturity:** As of April 30, 2026, there was $20,000 million of borrowings outstanding. The loan matures on September 2, 2027, subject to extension.\n    *   **Interest Rate:** The effective interest rate on outstanding borrowings was 4.58% as of March 31, 2026.\n*   **xAI Revolving Line of Credit:**\n    *   **Terms:** Entered in April 2024 and amended through March 2026, increasing the borrowing capacity from $150 million to $250 million.\n    *   **Status:** No borrowings during the three months ended March 31, 2026 and 2025, or during 2025. Letters of credit issued were $145 million.\n    *   **Interest Rate:** 30-day average SOFR +