    tool_call=ToolCall(
        id='call_a5a34095f55c4abebecda4c2',
        call_id=None,
        name='retrieve_information',
        args='{"prompt":"What information is disclosed in {{spacex_s1}} about the Spectrum Transaction with EchoStar, the FCC approval, and any qualitative discussion of strategic transactions or partnerships that lack specific quantitative financial details?"}',
        parsed_args={
            'prompt': 'What information is disclosed in {{spacex_s1}} about the Spectrum Transaction with EchoStar, the FCC approval, and any qualitative discussion of strategic transactions or partnerships that lack specific quantitative financial details?'
        }
    ),
    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# Information Disclosed in the Preamble Regarding Supply Chain Purchase Order Risks and the EchoStar Spectrum Transaction\n\n## Supply Chain Purchase Order Risks\n\nThe Preamble discloses the following regarding supply chain risks:\n\n- The company **generally does not have long-term binding and enforceable purchase orders** for parts and raw materials.\n- The **timing and magnitude of purchase orders beyond the short term is difficult to accurately project**.\n- Because of the absence of long-term purchase orders, **future purchases may result in material cash commitments**.\n- Readers are directed to the **"Risk Factors"** section of the prospectus for additional information about this risk.\n\n---\n\n## The $19.6 Billion EchoStar Spectrum Transaction\n\n### Agreement and Parties\n\n- On **September 7, 2025**, the Company entered into a **License Purchase Agreement** (the "Spectrum License Purchase Agreement") with **Spectrum Business Trust 2025-1** (a Nevada Business Trust, the "Trust") and **EchoStar Corporation** ("EchoStar").\n- The transactions contemplated thereby are collectively referred to as the **"Spectrum Transaction"** (or "Spectrum Transactions").\n\n### Amendment\n\n- On **November 5, 2025**, the parties **amended and restated** the Spectrum License Purchase Agreement to include EchoStar\'s licenses for **up to 15 MHz of additional unpaired AWS-3 spectrum**.\n- This amendment **increased the total consideration by $2,600 million**, from an original $17,000 million to a **total of $19,600 million**.\n- The cash payoff consideration, two-step transfer process, debt service payments, trust structure, and maintenance obligations remained unchanged.\n\n### Spectrum Being Acquired\n\n- The Company agreed to purchase EchoStar\'s rights and licenses related to an **aggregate of 50 MHz of spectrum** in frequency ranges **2000–2020, 2180–2200, 1915–1920, and 1995–2000** (the "AWS-4 and H-Block Licenses"), granted by the FCC.\n- Together with the amended AWS-3 spectrum, the total acquisition encompasses **65 MHz of spectrum** in the United States as well as certain global Mobile Satellite Service spectrum licenses.\n- The acquisition also includes certain **international authorizations, filings, concessions, licenses, rights and priorities** related to that spectrum and certain associated assets (collectively, the **"Foreign Assets"**).\n\n### Total Consideration Structure\n\nThe total consideration of approximately **$19.6 billion** consists of two components:\n\n| Component | Amount | Details |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Equity** | ~$11.1 billion | Payable through issuance of approximately **261.8 million shares** of Class A common stock at a **fixed value of $42.40 per share** |\n| **Debt Payoff** | Up to $8.5 billion | Related to the payoff of designated EchoStar debt, with any **shortfall below $8.5 billion to be paid in cash** |\n\n- The **allocation of cash and equity consideration is subject to certain adjustments** based on the amount of EchoStar debt satisfied at or prior to closing.\n- One chunk references pre-stock-split figures of approximately **52.4 million shares at $212 per share**, noting these amounts do not give effect to the 2026 Stock Split.\n\n### Two-Step Trust Transfer Process\n\nThe transfer of the AWS-4 and H-Block Licenses occurs in two steps:\n\n1. **Spectrum Transfer Closing**: The AWS-4 and H-Block Licenses are transferred by **EchoStar to the Trust**.\n2. **Spectrum Acquisition Closing**: The AWS-4 and H-Block Licenses are transferred by **the Trust to the Company**.\n\n- The **Foreign Assets** will be transferred **directly to the Company** at the Spectrum Acquisition Closing, to the extent required regulatory approvals have been obtained by such date.\n- The failure to obtain such approvals for the Foreign Assets **will not delay or prevent** the Spectrum Acquisition Closing.\n\n### Credit Agreement and Trust Loan Mechanics\n\n- On **September 7, 2025**, concurrent with the Spectrum License Purchase Agreement, the Company and the Trust entered into a **Credit Agreement**.\n- Upon the Spectrum Transfer Closing, the Company agreed to **loan to the Trust** (via loans cancelable at six-month intervals) funds to be used by the Trust to **make debt service payments on EchoStar\'s debt** through at least November 30, 2027, but in no event later than November 30, 2028.\n- These loans are **secured on a junior lien basis** by the AWS-4 and H-Block Licenses.\n\n### Regulatory Approvals and Closing Conditions\n\n- The **FCC approved** the Spectrum Transaction on **May 12, 2026**.\n- Completion is subject to the satisfaction or waiver of **customary closing conditions**, including receipt of certain consents and approvals from the **FCC** and the **Department of Justice ("DOJ")**.\n- The Spectrum License Purchase Agreement also provides for **specified termination rights**.\n\n### Expected Closing Date\n\n- The Spectrum Acquisition Closing is **expected to occur on or about November 30, 2027**, subject to other closing conditions.\n\n### Status as of December 31, 2025\n\n- As of December 31, 2025, the **Spectrum Transfer Closing had not yet occurred**.\n- As a result, the Company was **not yet obligated to make any payments** under the Credit Agreement with the Trust.\n\n### Accounting Treatment\n\n- Once the Spectrum Transfer Closing occurs, the Spectrum Transactions **will be recognized as acquired intangible assets**.\n\n### Financing Upon Closing\n\n- Upon closing, the Company intends to either **use cash and cash equivalents on hand** or **seek alternative financing sources**.\n\n### Strategic Purpose and Context\n\n- The spectrum acquisition supports the company\'s **Starlink Mobile Gen2 services**, including broadband data and IoT connectivity.\n- Combined with the deployment of **V2 Mobile satellites** in 2027 and optimized 5G protocols, the wider bandwidth operations enabled by this spectrum purchase are expected to **increase capacity by orders of magnitude** compared to the first-generation constellation.\n- The acquisition provides **very senior ITU priority** for international frequency coordination for the V2 Mobile constellation.\n- Until regulatory approvals are obtained, the Company signed a **coordination agreement with EchoStar** to obtain the protection of its senior ITU priority rights until the authorizations transfer.\n- The Company has received the relevant **license transfer approval from the FCC** for the United States and expects to receive remaining necessary U.S. regulatory authorizations in the **second or third quarter of 2026**.\n- Internationally, the Company has filed applications in nearly every country in which it intends to operate Gen2 service, with approvals granted in a limited number of jurisdictions to date.\n\n### Exclusion from Current Financial Representations\n\n- The prospectus explicitly states that its information **does not reflect** the payment of shares of Class A common stock and cash consideration which would occur upon closing of the Spectrum Transaction.\n- The Spectrum Transaction is also referenced in the company\'s **non-cancelable contractual commitments**, which are payable in cash and Class A Common Stock, and are included in the total commitments of **$25,451 million** (with $21,476 million due in 2027, aligning with the expected closing date).\n\n### Risk Factors Associated with the Transaction\n\n- There can be **no assurance** that closing conditions will be satisfied or waived in a timely manner, or at all.\n- Even if completed, there can be no assurance that the EchoStar spectrum purchase will be **sufficient to meet the company\'s growing need** for spectrum licenses.\n- The Company may be unable to find other parties to provide additional spectrum licenses on acceptable terms.\n- The Company must secure the **global right to use the spectrum** acquired from EchoStar from a number of international telecommunications regulators, with no assurance such authorizations will be granted.\n- The acquisition is listed among strategic transactions (alongside xAI, Tesla/Intel Terafab collaboration, and Cursor) that **may not achieve anticipated benefits, synergies, or strategic objectives**, and may present **unforeseen liabilities or disruptions**.',
        error=None,
        metadata=None,
